ound saying =E2=80=9Cwe structured this merger to do a short squeeze=E2=80=
=9D; you have to have some corporate finance reason for it. So the SEC=C2=
=A0<em>also=C2=A0</em>complains that they=C2=A0<em>didn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em=
>mention the short squeeze in their official communications to shareholders=
:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Specifically, Brda failed to =
disclose, and failed to cause Torchlight to disclose, the following in Torc=
hlight=E2=80=99s proxy statements and other public filings and statements: =
(1) that the Preferred Dividend was intended to cause, and to lead investor=
s to believe, that there would be a short squeeze and an increase in Torchl=
ight=E2=80=99s stock price; (2) that Brda believed the Preferred Dividend w=
ould cause a short squeeze and/or temporarily inflate Torchlight=E2=80=99s =
stock price; (3) that the potential for a short squeeze and/or temporary in=
flation of Torchlight=E2=80=99s stock price=C2=A0were reasons that Brda and=
 Torchlight considered in approving the merger and Preferred Dividend and r=
ecommending that shareholders approve the same; (4) Brda=E2=80=99s plan to,=
 and/or the potential that Torchlight would, deploy the ATM Offering; and (=
5) that, in connection with negotiations over the merger and Preferred Divi=
dend, Torchlight and Meta I discussed the Preferred Dividend=E2=80=99s pote=
ntial to cause a short squeeze, its potential to temporarily inflate Torchl=
ight=E2=80=99s stock price, and Brda=E2=80=99s plan to use an ATM Offering =
to raise funds from investors.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>That is, it was market manipulation for Brda and Palikaras to go around te=
