om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Hunterbrook</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As a person who works in media and wri=
tes about finance, I continue to be <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/35834494.260285/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlua=
W9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMDIvYS1oZWRnZS1mdW5kLXRoYXQtcy1hbHNvLWEtbmV3c3Bh=
cGVyP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MjUyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJ=
jZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDYyNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4b830ec1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">fascinated by Hunterbrook</a>, the =
newspaper that is also a hedge fund, the=C2=A0intersection of my interests.=
 When Hunterbrook launched earlier this year, my assumption was that it wou=
ld look more or less like an activist short fund: It would investigate comp=
anies, find out bad stuff about them, short their stocks, publish its findi=
ngs, and profit when the stocks went down. And in fact that has often been =
its model.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But, from the beginning, Hunterb=
rook emphasized that there were other possibilities. One thing it could do,=
 sometimes, is just be a newspaper: It could investigate companies, find=C2=
=A0out bad stuff about them,=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>short their stocks, pub=
lish its findings, and, you know, afflict the comfortable and comfort the a=
fflicted. Sometimes the crack reporters that you hire for their ability to =
find scandals will find a scandal, but it won=E2=80=99t be a scandal you ca=
n=C2=A0<em>trade=C2=A0</em>on; sometimes the market doesn=E2=80=99t care ab=
out a company=E2=80=99s labor practices in faraway countries. And then you =
publish the story anyway, to build credibility as a news source and to make=
 your crack reporters feel good about what they=E2=80=99re doing. A number =
of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35834494.260285=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMTYvdH=
J1bXAtbWVkaWEtaGFzLW1vcmUtc3RvY2stY29taW5nP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MjUyNF9NT05FWVNUV=
UZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDYy=
NSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9b65abdb" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">Hunterbrook=E2=80=99s stories so far</a>=C2=A0have looked like this: Act=
ivist short reports but without the shorting.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">A third model that Hunterbrook has emphasized is that it could trade=C2=
=A0<em>commodities=C2=A0</em>based on its reporting. The form is something =
like: You hire the only foreign correspondent in a faraway country that is =
the leading=C2=A0producer of unobtainium, she learns that a coup is in the =
offing and the new military junta will ban unobtainium exports,=C2=A0you go=
 long unobtainium futures, you publish her story, the price of unobtainium =
spikes, you profit.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a></p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This strikes me as a pretty good model=
, when you put it like that, but how often are your crack reporters really =
going to get advance notice of market-moving coups in commodity-exporting c=
ountries? If you could industrialize that it would be pretty cool, for you,=
 but pretty bad, for the commodity-exporting countries. Your investor lette=
r would be like =E2=80=9Cwe had a great quarter, driven by continuing stron=
g coup activity.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway=C2=A0<a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35834494.260285/aHR0cHM=
6Ly9obnRyYnJrLmNvbS9uaWNrZWwtaW4tbmV3LWNhbGVkb25pYS8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB9400d749" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">Hunterbrook=E2=80=99s latest report</a> yesterday isn=
=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>quite=C2=A0</em>that, but it does begin with a secret f=
light that might disrupt nickel supplies:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">Over the weekend, a jet departed New Caledonia, the French terri=
tory midway between Australia and Fiji. But it was nowhere to be found on p=
ublic flight trackers, according to transponder data examined by Hunterbroo=
k Media.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The plane seems to have crept into=
 the night sky with its transponder off, reportedly carrying detained pro-i=
ndependence activists secretly bound for mainland France.</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">As news broke of the flight, independence activists sparked =
fresh riots in New Caledonia. The conflict threatens to disrupt the fragile=
 peace of recent weeks after months of protests and uncertainty in the glob=
al nickel market. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That conflict i=
mpacted nickel production on the island. Due to New Caledonia=E2=80=99s sig=
nificant output, commodity analysts cited the unrest as a factor contributi=
ng to the spring surge in global nickel prices.</p></blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">There are some images of buildings on fire. Hunterbrook i=
s long nickel.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cells=
