s about 9.3%</a> of Hess=E2=80=99s stock, and it seems like a stretch to su=
ggest that he was, like, bribed into choosing Goldman as the company=E2=80=
=99s financial adviser with the promise of a board seat. Probably he wanted=
 the best deal for Hess, and also liked Goldman=E2=80=99s work.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s funny, there is an old-timey model of inv=
estment banking in which=C2=A0<em>of course=C2=A0</em><a href=3D"https://li=
